The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                                         3                                                                                      The City Diary
                A 27-year-old homemaker was allegedly burnt to death by her in-laws in Phoolbagan on Friday. Police said neighbours took Mamata Shaw to NRS Medical College and Hospital where doctors declared her dead.  amataa mother-in-law Basanti and sister-in-law Anju were arrested following a complaint by her parents alleging that Mamatas in-laws had killed her for dowry. Husband Manoj and his brother are absconding.     Mamata Banerjee will flag off an exhibition train at Howrah on May 9 to mark the 150th birth anniversary of Rabindranath Tagore. The exhibition will focus on Tagores life, works and philosophy and tour various parts of the country for a year.   alcutta University will organise an exhibition of Tagores paintings and hold seminars and a cultural function on its premises on May 9 to launch a year-long celebration for the poets 150th year.     The Air India office at 39 Chittaranjan Avenue will remain closed on Sundays from May 9.     The city police arrested the deputy vice-president of a Mumbai-based firm on Friday on the charge of selling Calcutta resident Paromita Rauts shares without her consent. The cops said Anup Goel had also forged Rauts signature to authorise the sale of shares worth Rs 3 lakh.                                                                                                                                               
